basil, pea, and potato soup recipe:
- Boil 12 chopped fingerling potatoes for 20 minutes, and boil 4 cups of fresh english peas for 5 minutes, then set both aside - Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium-low heat, add 1 cup chopped shallots for 8 to 10 minutes, then add 3 chopped garlic cloves in the last 2-3 minutes - Add 6 cups water, 3-4 tsp of vegetable better than bouillon, 1 tsp salt, and 0.5 tsp pepper. Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat to medium-low and cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes. - Remove the broth from the heat, add 0.5 cup basil and 0.25 cup parmesan, then pour broth into a blender - blend the mixture (excluding the peas and potatoes) - put the blended broth back in the pot, add peas and potatoes, bring to a boil, then remove from heat - garnish with parmesan, chives, basil, etc

Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat to medium-low and cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes. - Remove the broth from the heat, add 0.5 cup basil and 0.25 cup parmesan, then pour broth into a blender - blend the mixture (excluding the peas and potatoes) - put the blended broth back in the pot, add peas and potatoes, bring to a boil, then remove from heat - garnish with parmesan, chives, basil, etc
